  "title": "Creative Designer",
  "description": "<p>Listed amongst Marketing Magazine's Creative Agencies of the Year, PROTOCOL is a creative agency built for the bleeding edge of culture.</p><p>We are a proudly local, award-winning agency that has worked with global brands and local institutions such as the Singapore Art Museum, Luckin, the Singapore Kindness Movement, SingPost, Mandai, Meiji, Starhub, giga, Nestlé, 1664 Blanc, Singapore Grand Prix, amongst others.</p><p><strong>The role</strong></p><p>The designer will provide art direction, illustration and graphic design work across our portfolio of accounts with the following scope of work.</p><ul><li>Providing art direction, graphic design, Illustration and layout of social media content across all formats across ATL/BTL, digital and social formats ranging from static, animation, photography, web development and video productions for our production subsidiary UNMASTERED and our in-house cafe/art gallery Main Street Commissary, amongst other creative properties</li><li>Storyboarding, conceptualising & design of style frames for animation/production content for production</li><li>Ensure output matches the brand intent and messaging as well as the level of quality agency work should entail</li><li>Art direction for all visual communication related work be it internal merchandise projects or photography/production work</li><li>Support the team in matters of conceptualisation and ideation across all forms of social media & creative content</li><li>Regularly present creative campaigns to clients</li><li>Prepare design solutions for internal and external presentations</li><li>Participate in the entire production process to ensure integrity of final product (print, video, or digital production).</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree or Diploma in Graphic Design or equivalent</li><li>Keen sense of aesthetic design, colour and typography</li><li>Have a strong design portfolio (preferably showcased online)</li><li>Proficient in Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign & Freehand</li><li>Knowledge in Web design is an advantage.</li><li>A good eye for photography</li><li>Being well-tuned to popular culture, new design trends and techniques</li><li>Able to work under pressure and manage workloads effectively.</li></ul>",
